      "narrative": "## 2026-06-07 Daily Report\n\n**Roster:** No changes since yesterday — 150 strategies total (144 enabled, 6 disabled). All 13 open action items remain PROPOSED. The kill backlog is 5 days old with zero executions.\n\n### Headline: Pipeline Stalled — Day 5; v25 Edge Recovered; 50+ INVALID Strategies Still Running\n\nThe T+30 callback delivered only 2 trades today before going silent (last callback 1,136 seconds ago, worsening from 986s yesterday). Diagnose verdict: PIPELINE_STALLED — graduations arrive normally but the PriceCollector → StrategyManager wiring is silent. This is at least the 5th consecutive stall day. The investigate action item (ai-2026-06-06-002) is still PROPOSED with no code fix deployed. All numbers below are carried forward from yesterday's snapshot; no new shadow trades were collected today due to the stall.\n\n### v25-bot-excl-climbing: Edge Recovered — Promotion Proposal Renewed\n\nThe watchlist hold (ai-2026-06-02-006) was justified when the edge flag was DECAYING for 4 days (Jun 2–5). As of Jun 6's data, the flag has reverted to STRENGTHENING (last_25 mean = +5.57% vs overall mean = -5.48%). All 4 promotion gates clear: n=619, drop3=+1.065 SOL, total=+3.386 SOL, monthly=+4.26 SOL/mo. Composite score = 92.1 (highest in the roster).\n\n**Caution:** The monthly run rate has declined sharply over the past week — from +12.56 SOL/mo (May 31) to +4.26 SOL/mo (Jun 6). The strategy is above the 3.75 bar, but only barely, and the trajectory is concerning. Panel 11 (combo-level regime stability) returned 0 rows — the regime gate cannot be verified this cycle. Recommend the operator promote v25 to a live trial with a 7-day watch period; if monthly run rate drops below 3.75 at next evaluation, re-evaluate.\n\n### Kill Backlog: 50+ INVALID Strategies Still Enabled (5-Day Escalation)\n\nFifty-plus strategies with n≥100 and drop3≤0 remain active. Oldest kill proposals are now 5 days old (June 2). The most expensive unexecuted kills:\n\n-